  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 7, 10, 21, 25, 6.792006}", 
    "history" -> {"14.3", "15.0", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickState[u] represents a fermionic Gaussian pure state without pairing \
correlation. The particles in the state occupy the dressed modes \
characterized by the isometric rectangular matrix u. WickState[n -> f] \
represents the vacuum state of the Fock space for n fermion modes with global \
phase factor f; or the null state if f = 0. WickState[{Null, n}] \
WickState[n->phase] represents the null state of the Fock space for n fermion \
modes. WickState[{n1, n2, ...}, n] returns a WickSate object corresponding to \
the computational basis state Ket[{n1, n2, ...}] of m fermion modes. If the \
list of occupation numbers {n1, n2, ...} is shorter (or longer) than m, then \
the occupation numbers are cyclically repeated (or the list is simply cut).", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "WickState", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "WickState", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/WickState"}},
